Package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.accordion

Interface AccordionService

All Known Implementing Classes:
AccordionServiceImpl
public interface AccordionService
Provides high-level service operations for accordion UI components.

This interface extends the functionality of Accordion by offering default methods that rely on a AccordionComponentType‚Äîeither a user-specified type or a globally configured default. Service methods include expanding and collapsing accordion panels, checking whether panels are enabled, and retrieving their text content.

An implementation such as AccordionServiceImpl internally delegates to the framework‚Äôs ComponentFactory to create the correct Accordion instance based on the chosen AccordionComponentType. This design enables easy swapping of accordion implementations (e.g., Bootstrap-based, Material-based) without changing test code.
